# QoS Classes

Computed from resources (you don't set it). Decides **eviction order**.

- **Guaranteed** — every container sets CPU+mem, **requests == limits**.
- **Burstable** — some request/limit set, not Guaranteed (the 80%).
- **BestEffort** — **no** requests/limits at all.

## Eviction under memory pressure

> **BestEffort** → **Burstable** (over requests) → **Guaranteed** last. Cheapest insurance: **`requests == limits` on memory** → Guaranteed, left alone.

## OOMKilled vs Evicted

- **OOMKilled** — one **container** over its **limit**; kernel kills it. Fix: **raise limit / fix leak.**
- **Evicted** — whole **Pod** off a pressured **node**. Fix: **set requests / scale.**

> `kubectl describe pod` tells you which.
